description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a full time Community Psychiatric Nurse (CPN) working with younger people with Dementia (up to the age of 65 years) Band 6. The post involves completing initial cognitive assessments, giving diagnosis and subsequent follow up to service users and working closely with others involved in their care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that the successful applicant is a driver / car owner as the team works across the whole of the county, predominantly in service users own homes and also in clinics, where available. The office base is in Rushden Resource Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a small dedicated team which consist of CPN&#39;s, Occupational Therapist, Community Support Worker and Clinical Psychologists; working together to provide the best outcomes for service users and their families/carers. The candidate will need excellent communication skills and be able to liaise and work closely with many different disciplines, both within the trust and wider services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A good working knowledge of dementia is required and interest or previous experience in working with younger people is desirable, however there will be potential to increase expertise with support from our experienced, knowledgeable and dedicated team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant will need to demonstrate good leadership skills, bringing new initiatives, skills and ideas to the service, as well as providing supervision to other members of the team and mentorship to students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are able to offer a range of in house training opportunities, including management and leadership training and actively encourage staff to engage with further academic opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jenny Kerti Team Manager 07500020306&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;addressjenny.kerti@nhft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
